Ptolemaic King of Egypt 🦅 Ptolemy III Euergetes AE hemiobol with the classic eagle standing on a thunderbolt on the reverse. A lot of these coins have a circular indentation on each side which is thought to be from the preparation of the flan before the coin was struck with imagery. A tool would hold the flan in place as it was rotated in a circular motion to help cut off the edges making sure the coin reaches it correct dimensions. Ptolemy III was a king from 246-222 BC making this coin over 2,200 years old. #ancientcoin • #ancientcoins • #ancientart • #ptolemaiccoins • #ptolemyiiievergetes • #headyart

This Medahpack pulls out all the stunts ive learned in my travels through bag forming and sewing in general. From the clean parallel strap, to the side extensions for more room. From the thoughtful variations of fabric placement, to the design development itself from scratch. This bag does it all. It includes custom buttons for the main storage, which has 2 smaller pockets. It also includes velcro for the exterior pocket, which also features 2 smaller pockets inside. I also tried my hand at a side pocket for pens whathaveyou, and a little dangle for hanging keys or keychains.
.
2 pieces i am very proud of are the flap pocket for hidden treasures, sealed by velcro, and the redesigned ring placement for a smooth transformation between a casual shoulder bag to secure partypack.
.
I really am a proud art parent here. I hope there are souls out there that appreciate this as intimately as i do 🙏🙏🙏 so fierce
.
